Alex Uribe-Kuhn

Bio

I am a first-year PhD student in the School of Statistics at the University of Minnesota, and a trainee in the Data Science in Multi-Messenger Astrophysics (DSMMA) program.

Before moving to Minnesota, I received my MS in Statistics from the Statistics Department at Oregon State University where I was advised by Professor Sarah Emerson, and my BS in Mathematics from Western Washington University where I worked with Professor Kimihiro Noguchi.

Contact Information

E-mail: kuhn0218 at umn dot edu

Research Interests

  • Multiple hypothesis testing
  • Selective inference
  • Resampling methods
  • Large-scale and high-dimensional inference
  • Uncertainty quantification for machine learning procedures
